solution:
$\mathrm{Al}^{1++}+3 \mathrm{e}^{-} \longrightarrow \mathrm{Al}$
$\begin{aligned}
\text { Moles of electron } & =\frac{2 \times 30 \times 60}{96500} \\
& =\frac{36}{965}
\end{aligned}$
$\begin{aligned}
\text { Moles of } \mathrm{Al} & =\frac{36}{3 \times 965} \\
& =\frac{12}{965}
\end{aligned}$
$\text { Mass of } \mathrm{Al}=\frac{12}{965} \times 27$
$=0.336 \mathrm{gm}$

